                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">722.2315/2485: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 31, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>437. From the Under Secretary. Your 578, October 30, 11 a.m. The news contained
                    in your telegram is encouraging. I have spoken this morning with the Ambassador
                    of Ecuador urging that his Government cooperate in the sense indicated in the
                    last paragraph of your telegram under acknowledgement as soon as some concrete
                    opportunity is afforded, such as the return of prisoners. He felt sure that his
                    Government would work along these lines. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
